canonical:
  title: 賀登極表
  author: 尹瓘
  language: lzh
  text: 承乾御極亘地稱尊凡屬照臨僉同抃躍中賀 皇帝陛下廣淵成聖寬裕容人天啓羣心神器已歸於一德日資多福靈圖必保於千齡化被飛潛功均覆載臣逖居侯服欣遇帝初恭奉土宜修賀函而將致因拘朝檢馳使傳以頗稽仰惟撫育之仁俯諒忠勤之懇
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀登極表
  author: 尹瓘
  language: lzh
  text: 承乾御極。亘地稱尊。凡屬照臨。僉同抃躍。中賀。 皇帝陛下。廣淵成聖。寬裕容人。天啓羣心。神器已歸於一德。日資多福。靈圖必保於千齡。化被飛潛。功均覆載。臣逖居侯服。欣遇帝初。恭奉土宜。修賀函而將致。因拘朝檢。馳使傳以頗稽。仰惟撫育之仁。俯諒忠勤之懇。
korean:
  title: 하 등극 표
  author: 윤관
  language: kor
  text: 건괘(乾卦)를 받아 등극하시어 온 누리가 존호(尊號)를 일컬으니, 해가 조림(照臨)하는 곳에는 만민(萬民)이 모두 기뻐 춤추나이다. 중하(中賀) 황제폐하께서 넓고 깊으신 성덕(聖德)으로 너그러이 사람을 용납하시니, 하늘이 뭇사람의 마음을 인도하여 신기(神器)가 이미 한결같은 덕으로 돌아갔고, 날마다 많은 복을 지으시니 국운(國運)이 반드시 천 년을 보존될 것이며 황화(皇化)가 동물들에게까지 미치고 공업(功業)이 천지와 같으리이다. 신은 멀리 번국(藩國)에 살며 등극하시는 첫날을 기쁘게 맞아, 삼가 토산물(土産物)을 받들어 하표(賀表)를 올리려 하였으나 조정의 명령에 구애되어 사신(使臣)을 보냄이 자못 지체되었나이다. 우러러 어지신 덕으로 무육(撫育)해 주실 줄 믿사오니, 간절한 충근(忠勤)을 굽어 살펴 주소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0220&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 하 등극 표(賀登極表) : '
    value: 임금이 재위(在位)한 중에 공덕(功德)이 있으면 신하들이 칭송하여 아름다운 존호(尊號)를 올린다.
english:
  title: A Congratulatory Memorial on the Emperor's Accession to the Throne
  author: Yun Gwan
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Receiving the mandate of Heaven, the Emperor ascends the throne, and all the lands beneath proclaim his dignity. Wherever his benevolent gaze falls, the myriad people leap with joy and celebration.

    Your Imperial Majesty,

    With virtue as vast as the deep abyss and a heart as generous as the boundless sky, you embrace all people with grace. Heaven guides the hearts of the multitude, and the Celestial Mandate has been fulfilled through your singular virtue. Day by day you cultivate blessings abundant, and the fate of the realm shall surely endure for a thousand years. Your imperial influence reaches even the winged and crawling creatures, and your achievements match the magnitude of Heaven and Earth.

    Your humble servant, dwelling in a distant tributary state, joyfully welcomes this glorious inception of your reign. With reverence, I prepared to offer local tributes and present this memorial of congratulations, yet bound by the protocols of court, the dispatch of my envoy has suffered some delay. I humbly trust in your benevolent care and nurturing grace, and beseech you to regard with compassion this servant's sincere devotion and earnest loyalty.
  footnotes:
    - A congratulatory memorial on imperial accession (賀登極表) was traditionally presented by courtiers and regional lords when a new emperor ascended the throne, offering praise for his virtue and blessings for the stability of the realm.
